result.execSummary:
The defendant Peace C Dixon was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Reckless Driving-Cause Great Bodily Harm, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.62(4).
  • Knowingly Operating While Suspended (Cause Great Bodily Harm), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Peace C Dixon in court with attorney Richard J Carpenter.  Thomas L Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  
AS TO COUNT 1 and COUNT 2, Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant. 
AS TO COUNT 1
Defendant sentenced to serve 1 YEAR at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION. Credit for 0 days time served. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 2
Defendant sentenced to serve 1 YEAR at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, CONCURRENT to COUNT 1. Credit for 0 days time served. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 YEARS, CONCURRENT to COUNT 1.
-
Court orders defendant to serve 10 DAYS CONDITION TIME IN THE HOUSE OF CORRECTION as to COUNT 1.  Defendant to report to the House of Corrections on 05-09-2014 by 5:00pm.  Sentencing Referral Form SIGNED AND FILED.
